<TITLE> Govt to supervise prices in Ramadan </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 7 (bdnews24.com)The government will supervise markets to make sure the prices of essential commodities are within people's reach during Ramadan, the commerce minister said on Friday. Faruk Khan told reporters after inaugurating a Bonsai exhibition in the capital that enough amount of essentials has been stockpiled. He advised the businessmen to should act responsibly in making profit as Ramadan is a month of frugality. Radiant Institute of Design is hosting the two-day Bonsai exhibition at Orchid Plaza in Dhanmondi. bd
